title: Summary - Hurricane Tammy (AT5/AL202023)
author: nhcwebmaster@noaa.gov (NHC Webmaster)
summary:
...TAMMY STRENGTHENS OVER OPEN WATERS... ...FORECAST TO BECOME A POWERFUL EXTRATROPICAL CYCLONE BY THURSDAY...
 As of 11:00 PM AST Tue Oct 24
 the center of Tammy was located near 24.9, -60.7
 with movement NE at 9 mph.
 The minimum central pressure was 976 mb
 with maximum sustained winds of about 85 mph.
